<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-32-1003 </DOCNO><TEXT>The discussion about the input of pollutants in ecosystems currently focusseson emissions entailing the formation of acids and photooxidants, followedby heavy-metal emissions. In Europe, by far the greatest part of thoseemissions results from anthropogenic activities. The paper describeslarge-scale immissions and depositions and establishes an atmosphericsulfur balance for Europe. Propagation models described are TADAP andthe EUM model of the German Weather Service.</TEXT></DOC>